<h2>
    <strong>Best Time of Year to Catch Largemouth Bass Near Gresham</strong>
</h2>
<p>
    Fishing largemouth bass is a seasonal sport, and timing your trips is essential for success:
</p>
<ul>
    <li>
        <strong>Spring (March–May):</strong> Bass move into shallower waters for spawning. Use slow-moving jigs and soft plastics.
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Summer (June–August):</strong> Early morning and late evening topwater action is unbeatable. Midday fishing is slower due to warmer water temps.
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Fall (September–October):</strong> Bass feed aggressively to fatten up for winter. Crankbaits and spinnerbaits work great.
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Winter (November–February):</strong> Coldwater slows bass metabolism. Fish deep and slow with drop-shot rigs or suspending jerkbaits.
    </li>
</ul>
